00:00:00.256 --> 00:00:02.840
<b>When you reach out to pull, push or lift,</b>

00:00:03.072 --> 00:00:05.632
<b>your body is designed to use on leg for strength</b>

00:00:05.888 --> 00:00:06.912
<b>and the other for balance.</b>

00:00:07.424 --> 00:00:10.279
<b>In Safety In Motion, the distance between your ankles </b>

00:00:10.280 --> 00:00:12.452
<b>is called your line of strength &amp; balance.</b>

00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:14.996
<b>When your upper body is over this line,</b>

00:00:15.069 --> 00:00:19.068
<b>you have both strength and balance </b>
<b>in the event of an unexpected push or pull.</b>

